WEBVTT

00:07:29.490 --> 00:07:31.712
I mean, even if
you're cavalier about privacy,

00:07:31.736 --> 00:07:34.331
I hope that you would admit
that's a step too far.

00:07:34.680 --> 00:07:37.188
SM: This is why I want
to keep my sex toys dumb.

00:07:37.212 --> 00:07:38.378
KH: That's great.

00:07:38.402 --> 00:07:40.068
We're all very glad to know that.

00:07:40.092 --> 00:07:41.540
(Laughter)

00:07:41.564 --> 00:07:43.598
SM: A data point I'm willing to share.

00:07:43.622 --> 00:07:45.345
(Laughter)

00:07:45.369 --> 00:07:48.339
The devices Kashmir bought
range from useful to annoying.

00:07:48.363 --> 00:07:50.156
But the thing they all had in common

00:07:50.180 --> 00:07:52.879
was sharing data with
the companies that made them.

00:07:52.903 --> 00:07:55.211
With email service providers
and social media,

00:07:55.235 --> 00:07:58.193
we've long been told that if it's free,
you're the product.

00:07:58.217 --> 00:08:00.224
But with the internet of things, it seems,